      <section>
       <title>Gold VIX</title>
       <subtitle>The Index of the Fear During the Terrorism Attacks</subtitle>
       <chapter>
         <paragraph>
              Nik Crepaldi, a financial adviser, found that the VIX index, also called "index of fear",
              has skyrocketed to 9.31% during the attacks in Paris, without any reason. The index measures the degree of
              nervousness of the bags: when it is high all sell, when everybody buys is low. Not only that, the VIX
              has shown an increase of 40% over the 5 days prior to the Paris attacks.</paragraph>
       </chapter>
